article.headline: Manhattan 90, Rider 73
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Peter Mulligan scored 21 points and CJ Anderson added 19, leading Manhattan to a 90-73 victory over Rider on Friday night. Arturo Dubois added 13 points, Kenny Minor finished with 12 and Jason Wingate and Jeff Xavier each scored 11 as Manhattan (11-11, 6-8 Metro-Atlantic Athletic Conference) snapped a three-game losing streak. Jerry Johnson scored 23 points to lead Rider (13-9, 9-4). Manhattan built a 35-32 lead by the break, but Rider closed within 37-36 on a jumper by Robert Taylor with 18:49 remaining. The Jaspers went on a 32-11 run that extended their lead to 22 points at 69-47 with 9:43 left. Rider cut the deficit to 76-68, on a 3-pointer by Johnson with 4:22 remaining, but Manhattan closed out the win with a 14-5 run.
